HEADWORD: Denticulation
<hw>Den*tic`u*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The state of being set with small notches or teeth.</def>
<rj><au>Grew.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot. & Zool.)</fld> <def>A diminutive tooth; a
denticle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dentiferous</ent>⟦br⟧
